franchise.name: DC Franchise Database
franchise.description: Total Drama franchise player statistics and performance data

players.name: Alejandro
players.story: Three finals, one crown. Strategic mastermind who finally won in Season 4 after two runner-up finishes. Known for alliance control, adaptability, and clutch fire-making performance.

players.name: Amy
players.story: Introduced on Rescue Island (Season 5), Amy weaponized the Amy/Samey feud to keep the tribe polarized, often becoming the swing point whenever the vote turned into chaos. She survived into the late game despite regular blowback (3 votes against) and even burned her Shot in the Dark at a key Tribal. Her run ended in Episode 11 when advantage/idol dynamics voided key votes and the numbers finally converged on her (Result: Amy eliminated, 2–1 (with 2 Dave votes voided)).

players.name: Anne Maria

notes: Gave extra vote to Jo from EoE

players.story: Betrayed by unbreakable partner Cameron in S3. Wasted idol on Zoey in S4 Episode 1, leading to early elimination.

players.name: B
players.story: Socially isolated pre-merge boot. Never formed alliances or meaningful connections.

players.name: Beardo
players.story: On Season 5’s pre-merge chaos, Beardo leaned into a low-profile social game and tried to stabilize early bonds, but never shook the perception of being expendable in a numbers crunch. With limited challenge impact and the tribe constantly scrambling around twists, he became the path-of-least-resistance boot. He was eliminated in Episode 3 in a vote where very few ballots actually counted (Beardo eliminated, 1–0 (effective)).

players.name: Beth

notes: Sent to RI on opening rocks; eliminated Episode 3 duel

players.story: Unlucky casualty of Galang’s first chaotic rock draw. Lost the first active duel and exited early.

players.name: Blaineley
players.story: A chaos agent turned integrated number through bonds with Mickey and Geoff. Went to rocks at merge, survived deep, then fell as the safe Final 5 consensus.

players.name: Brick
players.story: Won first individual immunity at merge. Solid mid-merge player with strong bonds but no strategic control.

players.name: Bridgette
players.story: Social heart of Season 1 with multiple immunities and idol. First boot in Season 2 due to tribe disagreements.

players.name: Brody

notes: Voted out Episode 14 (4–2) after earlier swap boot to RI
keyMoments: Returned from RI at merge with clue
Cut 4–2 as final push against Surfers momentum

players.story: Perennial target and comeback kid who returned at merge, won immunity, and influenced key votes. Eventually cut as a popularity and challenge threat after drawing 26 votes across the season.

players.name: Cameron
players.story: Strategic mastermind who made brutal move voting out unbreakable partner Anne Maria in S3. Strong strategic player across both seasons.

players.name: Cody
players.story: First casualty of the Gophers' internal alliance war. Voted out 6-5 in Episode 6 when Leshawna unexpectedly flipped.

players.name: Courtney
players.story: Volatile gameplay across three seasons. Multiple meltdowns and catastrophic extra vote misplay in S4 led to elimination.

players.name: Crimson
players.story: Half of the Gothic Hearts duo whose medevac reshaped early dynamics and left Ennui unanchored.

players.name: Dakota
players.story: Fan Favorite winner in S3 despite pre-merge exit. First boot in S4, became first and only person to quit Edge of Extinction.

players.name: Dave
players.story: Dave was a central strategic connector for the Lulu side of Season 5, mixing steady positioning with real challenge value (2 wins, including 1 immunity). In the late game he survived a critical Tribal by playing Shot in the Dark successfully, but the next wave of idol chaos flipped the math against him. He was eliminated in Episode 12 when a 3–3 vote became a clean boot after idol cancellation (Result: Dave eliminated, 3–0 effective (3–3 on paper with idol cancellation)).

players.name: Dawn
players.story: Consensus target Episode 9. Even allies voted her out when she became the agreed-upon target.

players.name: DJ
players.story: Made merge and jury in S2 after early boot in S1. Social friction and conflicts prevented deeper runs.

players.name: Duncan
players.story: Season 2 Winner. Survived constant targeting through clutch immunity wins. Previous winner eliminated at Final 6 in S4.

players.name: Dwayne

keyMoments: Cut as the merge overlap boot

players.story: Steady ‘dad glue’ who bridged pairs on Galang. Became the overlap boot at merge when factions needed a justifiable target.

players.name: Ella
players.story: Ella’s Rescue Island run was defined by pure social warmth and early connection-building, but that visibility made her an easy name when the tribe needed a clean vote. With the game already drifting toward advantage paranoia, she couldn’t find a shield in time. She was eliminated in Episode 2 on a tight pre-merge vote (Ella eliminated, 2–1).

players.name: Emma

notes: Re-entry penalty used on Anne Maria
Rock-draw casualty Episode 10; later eliminated on RI
keyMoments: Lost via rocks in a deadlock

players.story: Composed strategist who won the first merge immunity and waged a season-long feud with Ryan. Lost to rocks in the merge deadlock and couldn’t fight back from RI.

players.name: Ennui

notes: Voted out Episode 3 (6–3) to RI; later eliminated

players.story: Goth outsider who became a focus-and-duels threat on RI. His pre-merge boot broke Brody’s social leverage.

players.name: Eva
players.story: Voted out 6-4 in Episode 3 as challenge liability. Social friction prevented alliance formation.

players.name: Ezekiel

notes: Legendary idol play on Alejandro at merge
Lost fire-making to Alejandro at F4

players.story: Finalist in S1 who lost fire-making. Made legendary idol play saving Alejandro in S2 but fell to social isolation.

players.name: Geoff

notes: Voted out Episode 16 (4–1) after returning from RI
keyMoments: Anchored early Galang core with Mickey/Ryan
Cut 4–1 as the late jury threat

players.story: Charismatic social hub of Surfers Bros who bridged factions early and mid-game. Returned from Redemption late but was cut as a jury threat once idols and loyalties converged.

players.name: Gwen
players.story: Massive improvement arc: 16th → 8th → 4th. Set franchise record with 4 consecutive immunity wins. Lost when couldn't win fire-making.

players.name: Harold
players.story: Found Advantage Menu in S4. Betrayed by Cameron (strong bond) at F8 revote. Won immunity Episode 10.

players.name: Heather

notes: Lost to Owen on Exile Beach

players.story: Strategic player across three seasons. Found 2 idols in S1. Multiple major fights led to pre-merge exit in S4.

players.name: Izzy
players.story: Eliminated 5-4 in Episode 7 after tribe swap. Personal hatred with Beth led to elimination.

players.name: Jacques

keyMoments: Engineered Kitty’s idol burn at merge
Won 4 immunities to steer late votes
Chose the Final 4 tie path that sent Kelly out

players.story: Played a low-target, high-control game, bridging rival blocs and weaponizing relationships while taking only 2 votes all season. He clinched control with 4 immunity wins and a masterful endgame that set the Final 4 tie in his favor.

players.name: Jasmine
players.story: Jasmine brought a steady, survival-first presence to the early Belo/Reba chaos, attempting to keep the tribe focused while smaller rivalries pulled votes in different directions. Without advantages or a dominant alliance to lock her in, she became a convenient compromise boot once numbers got messy. She exited in Episode 5 (Jasmine eliminated, 2–1).

players.name: Jay

keyMoments: Sat in the Final 4 tie that booted Kelly

players.story: Rode or died with Mickey while building cross-tribe bridges, surviving chaotic votes and a rock-draw episode. Reached the end as the loyal lieutenant with fewer signature moves than his allies.

players.name: Jo

advantages: Extra vote from Anne Maria (EoE), used Ep 8

players.story: Most hated player with 4 EXTREME HATRED relationships. FAN FAVORITE winner in S4 for chaotic entertainment value.

players.name: Josee
players.story: Hyper-competitive firebrand whose meltdowns isolated her on Galang. Voted out cleanly despite challenge value.

players.name: Junior

notes: Voted out Episode 4 (6–2) to RI; later eliminated on RI

players.story: Eager underdog who battled through RI duels but couldn’t escape the ‘liability’ label. His exit weakened Dwayne’s leverage.

players.name: Justin

notes: First juror after Ezekiel's idol play
Found idol early but didn't play it

players.story: First boot in S1 despite finding idol. First juror in S2 after idol play chaos.

players.name: Katie
players.story: Played solid pre-merge game as part of MAPLV with Sadie. Found Hidden Immunity Idol.

players.name: Kelly

notes: Eliminated Final 4 (2–2 tie, 1–1 revote, lost fire-making)
keyMoments: Found and correctly played Tadhana idol at swap

players.story: Sponsor strategist who found the Tadhana idol, nuked a swap vote to save herself, and rebuilt into a late-game power. Fell at fire-making after clashing with Mickey and threading multiple alliances.

players.name: Kitty

notes: Voted out Episode 11 (3–2–2–1–1) to RI (idol previously burned on Jacques)
keyMoments: Played idol on Jacques at merge
Sent to RI in a 5-way split vote

players.story: Social spark of Sis4ever who found the merge idol but burned it on Jacques. Became a split-vote magnet and was sent to RI in a chaotic round.

players.name: Leonard

notes: Voted out Episode 2 (5–3) to RI; eliminated Episode 4

players.story: Self-sacrificing partner who swapped to RI for Tammy, then became the easy ‘liability’ cut and lost the duel later.

players.name: Leshawna
players.story: First juror in S1. Second boot in S2 despite unbreakable bond with Noah in S1.

players.name: Lightning

notes: WORST idol play ever (wasted on Emma)

players.story: Part of TRIPLE IDOL TRIBAL in S4. Worst idol play in S3 (wasted on Emma who got 0 votes).

players.name: Lindsay
players.story: WINNER of Season 1. Social queen who maintained unbreakable bonds without burning bridges. Third place in S2.

players.name: Mary

notes: Idol casualty Episode 7 (Kelly’s idol negated majority)

players.story: Cold planner who refused to swap for Beth, then pushed liability cuts. Was idoled out at the swap.

players.name: Max
players.story: Max leaned into a disruptive, chaos-friendly game on Season 5, frequently pulling attention and forcing others to account for worst-case twists. He gained Safety Without Power, which shaped vote calculus even when he couldn’t fully cash it in for long-term security. Eventually the table got tired of the volatility and he was voted out in Episode 8 (Max eliminated, 5–3).

players.name: Mickey

keyMoments: Played idol on Jay at Final 5

players.story: The loyal core of AnxietyBro, he paired tight social bonds with steady challenge value and deep protection. An endgame idol on Jay and consistent positioning brought him to the end.

players.name: Mike
players.story: REBUILT unbreakable bond with Zoey in S4. Victim of Sierra's perfect idol play (10 votes cancelled).

players.name: Noah
players.story: Part of TRIPLE IDOL TRIBAL in S4. BETRAYED by unbreakable partner Alejandro at F9. Bitter jury vote.

players.name: Owen
players.story: Sent to Exile Beach in S1, won return but medically evacuated. Third boot in S2 after idol chaos.

players.name: Rodney
players.story: Rodney played Season 5 like a classic mid-game grinder: visible, socially active, and constantly trying to grab tools that could flip a vote. He notably secured Knowledge Is Power from a Journey, instantly spiking his threat level even without challenge dominance. Once the tribe decided he was too dangerous to keep around, he was voted out in Episode 7 (Rodney eliminated, 3–1).

players.name: Ryan

notes: Voted out Episode 12 (5–2–1) to Redemption; later eliminated on RI

players.story: Aggressive swing player who found an idol (burned it), won immunity, and steered pivotal mid-game votes before being consensused out for being too connected.

players.name: Sadie
players.story: Eliminated by rock draw despite never receiving a vote and voting correctly. Inseparable from Katie in MAPLV.

players.name: Sam
players.story: Most tragic exit - NEVER received a vote, voted correctly, eliminated by rock draw. Most unlucky player in franchise.

players.name: Samey
players.story: Samey’s Season 5 story is the underdog attempt to play her own game while the Amy rivalry kept dragging her into the spotlight. She picked up a Goodwill-style social leverage moment and tried to build safer bonds, but advantage chaos punished anyone without hard protection. In Episode 4, an idol cancelled multiple votes and she was eliminated on an ultra-thin effective count (Result: Samey eliminated 1–0 (effective) after idol cancels 4 votes).

players.name: Scarlett
players.story: Top strategic rank of Season 5 and a late power player, but lost the Final 4 fire-making duel.

players.name: Scott

notes: Perfect idol play at F5 (3 votes cancelled)
Only Duncan voted for him at FTC

players.story: Best player to never win. PERFECT IDOL PLAY after holding for 9 tribals (franchise record). Runner-up in S3, third place in S4.

players.name: Shawn
players.story: Shawn navigated Season 5 with a paranoid-but-prepared mindset, finding a Beware Idol on Belo and briefly holding real leverage at the merge. His risk-taking peaked when he used Shot in the Dark and lost his vote, putting him on the wrong side of the numbers. He was eliminated in Episode 9 (Shawn eliminated, 5–2), but not before becoming a real factor in the season’s advantage economy.

players.name: Sierra
players.story: Won EoE return in S4. Made PERFECT IDOL PLAY cancelling 10 votes - only 2 people didn't vote Sierra. Created 4 extreme hatreds.

players.name: Sky
players.story: Season 5 challenge MVP with 4 total challenge wins and 3 immunities; forced the late-game tempo but fell short in a 3–3 FTC tie.

players.name: Staci
players.story: Second boot. Multiple early conflicts prevented alliance formation. Challenge liability with no social capital.

players.name: Stephanie

notes: Voted out Episode 6 (6–1); threw an idol clue into the fire on RI
keyMoments: Burned an idol clue on RI
Voted out 6–1 after conflict with Jacques

players.story: Fierce competitor who clashed with Jacques and became a control vote casualty. Leaned into independence on RI to no avail.

players.name: Sugar
players.story: Sugar made one of the deepest runs of Season 5 by surviving constant heat (10 votes against) and leaning into a loud, chaos-driven social style that kept targets rotating. With the endgame dominated by idol-threat management, she repeatedly found herself in the crosshairs as players tried to simplify the board. She was eliminated in Episode 13 in a near-unanimous vote with a cancelled ballot (Sugar eliminated, 4–0 (with 1 Sky vote cancelled)).

players.name: Tammy

notes: Swap to RI in Ep2; eliminated on RI in Episode 5
keyMoments: Voted in twist to RI Day 1

players.story: Twist casualty who pinballed between camp and RI through pair swaps. Couldn’t convert survival into a return.

players.name: Topher
players.story: Topher’s Rescue Island run revolved around risk-reward mechanics: he took on a Beware-style disadvantage, forcing him to manage social fallout while dealing with limited voting power. Without immunity wins or an idol safety net, he became the merge’s stability target. He was eliminated in Episode 7 and became the season’s first juror (Topher eliminated, 5–1 (and becomes 1st juror due to being eliminated from).

players.name: Trent
players.story: Strong social player with multiple unbreakable bonds. Eliminated in double eliminations both seasons.

players.name: Tyler
players.story: Challenge liability voted out 8-4 in Episode 2. Unable to build strong social connections.

players.name: Zoey

notes: Perfect idol play saved Geoff (7 votes cancelled)
Made finals with zero votes against (1 cancelled)

players.story: UNPRECEDENTED social dominance with 3 unbreakable bonds at once in S4. Lost 6-7 to Alejandro in closest finale ever. Most socially connected player in franchise history.
